    <title>Self-Supervised Learning for Robotic Manipulation with
  Sparse Rewards</title>
    <summary>  This paper introduces a self-supervised learning framework for
robotic manipulation tasks operating under sparse reward signals.
We demonstrate improved sample efficiency through a combination
of contrastive learning and hindsight experience replay.
</summary>
